JO  - AMJ
SP  - 157
EP  - 159
VL  - 9
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a fictional interview with Grant Swinger, director of the Breakthrough Institute and chairman of the board of the Center for the Absorption of Federal Funds. Swinger stated the purpose of the Center for the Absorption of Federal Funds. He offered an overview of the work of the center toward the development of programs, procedures and goals for its member institutions. Details of the types of tests and examinations being developed by the center are also outlined.
