TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Research and Development Manager's Dilemma: Fact or Fiction
AU  - Steinmetz, Lawrence L.
Y1  - 1966/06/01
PY  - 1966
DA  - 1966/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255033
DO  - 10.5465/255033
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 145
EP  - 151
VL  - 9
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article addresses creative approaches to solving scientific and technological dilemmas. The article focuses on the relationship between a research and development (R&D) manager and his employees. Problems within the R&D environment such as a subordinate's loss of respect and the dilemmas an R&D manager might face, such as friction between himself and a bench scientist or feeling a loss of control, are considered. The article considers ways of solving these dilemmas through understanding the unique role of R&D scientists and motivating them to achieve, sometimes at the cost of the R&D manager's own technical advancement.
